Estimados Padres,

Gracias por sus esfuerzos heroicos para apoyar las escuelas de sus hijos y el proceso de aprendizaje durante los cierres debido a la pandemia de coronavirus. El Departamento de Educación de Nueva Jersey (Departamento) continúa los preparativos para las próximas etapas de la apertura de la escuela, y escuchar a los padres es una prioridad del Departamento. Por favor, tómese unos minutos para completar la encuesta en el siguiente enlace: https://es.surveymonkey.com/r/7VM29CM
Agradecemos recibir sus respuestas antes del Lunes 8 de Junio.

Si tiene alguna pregunta, por favor póngase en contacto con la Oficina de Compromiso Cívico y Social del Departamento en civicandsocial@doe.nj.gov.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

Thank you for your heroic efforts to support your children’s schools and the learning process during closings due to the coronavirus pandemic. The New Jersey Department of Education (Department) continues preparations for the next stages of school opening, and hearing from parents is a Department priority. Please take a few minutes to complete the survey at the following link: https://es.surveymonkey.com/r/V8HZ2MQ
We appreciate receiving your responses by Monday, June 8th.

If you have any questions, please contact the Department’s Office of Civic and Social Engagement at civicandsocial@doe.nj.gov.

post_text:
Many of you may have noticed the majority of your child’s work being assigned online. However, there are still some classes that require some paper-based assignments.

Work drop-off/ pick-up is scheduled for Thursday, April 16 for grades PK, K, 2, and 4. All other grade levels are now assigning work online. Here are the times for families to pick-up on Thursday morning curbside:

9:00-10:00- student last name A-H
10:00-11:00- student last name I-Q
11:00-12:00- student last name R-Z

Also, any paperwork for Specialists from weeks 3-4 (such as art, music, health, PE, Spanish, speech) should be submitted by any grade level student this day.

Moving forward, a box will be placed out front near the main door, daily, beginning April 17. Families may drop-off work at your convenience. When leaving work in the box, please be sure to have the student's name and teacher's name on the assignments. The box will be emptied daily and work will be submitted to the teacher.

We appreciate your cooperation during this unique situation.

🐰The Pedricktown Fire Company will be escorting the Easter Bunny on the fire truck around the township on Friday April 10. The Easter Bunny will start to make his way around town ( including Auburn ) at 4pm. We will try and travel most of the populated areas for the kids. If you live on the outskirts of town or even in town and want to park at the Oldmans Township School , please feel free.The Oldmans Township School is allowing families to park in their parking lot for that day. Please observe social distancing. When you hear the fire truck coming, please come outside to see the Easter Bunny and wave. He’s happy to see everyone so close to Easter. 🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰

🥚🦋HAPPY EASTER 🦋🥚

post_text:
The third marking period ends on April 7. Report cards will be available for your view on April 9. Due to the school closure, we are asking parents and guardians to log-in to OnCourse Connect to view your child’s report card. The only exception to this is pre-kindergarten. Their report cards will be mailed.

For OnCourse Connect, you will need to know your username and password. If you do not remember your username, we are able to provide that to you. If you do not remember your password, you will need to use the "forgot password" reset feature in the OnCourse Connect portal. To reset your password through the portal, you will need to have an up to date email address in OnCourse. If you do not, please contact Mr. Cairns via email at dcairns@oldmans.org.

If for any reason you need a paper copy mailed, please email Mrs. Halter at halter@oldmans.org.
